<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7629440>
    dc:description "Fig. 41. Georeferenced collection records of Lasioglossum (D.) lepidii (Graenicher, 1927) (black squares) and predicted distribution by maximum entropy ecological niche modelling in Maxent (colour shading). Warmer colours indicate higher cloglog probability of occurrence. Because many coastal records lacked soil data, the model was generated without soil type as an environmental variable." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7629440/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7629558>
    dc:description "Fig. 96. Frons. A. Lasioglossum holzenthali sp. nov., ♀, roughened and dulled by crowded punctures without distinct interspaces. B. L. lepidii (Graenicher, 1927), ♀, smooth and shiny between punctures. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7629558/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7629610>
    dc:description "Fig. 119. Pleura. A. Lasioglossum lepidii (Graenicher, 1927), ♂, preëpisternum and hypoepimeron more finely punctate than mesepisternum. B. L. diabolicum sp. nov., ♂, preëpisternum and hypoepimeron as coarsely punctate as mesepisternum. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7629610/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

